node.text:
Sharing experiences like this with people you love make the memories even sweeter🌎😌✨

Photo shot by @chrisrlocke

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ANGELA | hiking + travel ↟ in Beautiful British Columbia with @angelaliggs, @juliiathompson, and @allaboutadventures. May be an image of 1 person and outdoors.

node.text:
It took us over four hours to hike here. There was only one other woman on the trail who told us she saw four bears so we were a bit spooked. We made noise and looked around us the entire hike up. It was exhausting… but dang.. once we saw this campsite at the top all of that faded away☺️

Hope you have a chance to get outside today, wherever you are in the world♥️🌎

Photo shot by @juliiathompson

node.text:
Summer always goes by in the blink of an eye—so make sure to seize every moment you get🥾

These are some clips from my most recent adventures. All in beautiful British Columbia♥️🇨🇦

If you’re here from the reels feed, follow me for more ↝ @angelaliggs

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ANGELA | hiking + travel ↟ in Beautiful British Columbia. May be an image of one or more people, mountain, sky and nature.

node.text:
Vancouver has its flaws but the fact that I can sit here, on a summit surrounded by mountain peaks, then walk into my apartment three hours later is pretty dang incredible. Forever blessed that the mountains are so close to home and that I feel so strongly for them♥️🏔

Photo shot by @juliiathompson

node.text:
📍My home away from home

Tag the person you want to go camping with😌⛺️

If you’re here from the reels feed, follow me for more ↝ @angelaliggs

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ANGELA | hiking + travel ↟ in Beautiful British Columbia with @angelaliggs, @juliiathompson, and @allaboutadventures. May be an image of lake and nature.

node.text:
Hazy days in the valley💚 Remember to be fire smart and not have campfires during the next couple months—especially during this extremely dry weather.

On average, 40% of wildfires in British Columbia are human-caused by activities like open burning, the use of engines/vehicles, dropping cigarettes, or anything else that creates sparks or a heat source. A campfire just isn’t worth it. 

I was camping last night and saw a fire on the other side of the lake. Don’t be those people🥺

Photo shot by @juliiathompson

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ANGELA | hiking + travel ↟ in Beautiful British Columbia with @explorecanada, @angelaliggs, @juliiathompson, @hellobc, @beautifuldestinations, @earthpix, @canada, @ourplanetdaily, @tourcanada, @earthfocus, @her.pnw.life, @roamtheplanet, @earthoutdoors, @womenwhoexplore, @allaboutadventures, @womenwhohike, @hikingtheglobe, @hikingbangers, and @wanderwomeninc. May be an image of one or more people and outdoors.

node.text:
My soul is the happiest when I’m high in the mountains (and even more so when I’m above the clouds)😌⛺️☁️ 

So grateful for experiences like this, to be out in nature and to watch Mother Earth put on a beautiful show. 

Photo shot by @juliiathompson
